Package: mc3logit
Type: Package
Title: Matched Case-Control Conditional Logit with Permutation Inference
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("George G.", "Vega Yon", role = c("aut")),
    person("Sima", "Najafzadeh", , "sima.njf1376@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Description: Implements permutation-based inference for matched
    case-control conditional logistic regression models, developed to
    study peer effects in police officers' use-of-force behavior (see
    Ouellet, Hashimi, and Vega Yon (2023) <doi:10.1007/s10940-022-09546-9>).
    Regular asymptotic standard errors for conditional logit models can be
    unreliable when matched sets (strata) are small, which is common when
    strata are, e.g., officers co-present at the same incident. This
    package addresses that by permuting outcomes within strata to build an
    empirical reference distribution for the model coefficients, following
    the permutation approach used by Ridgeway (2016)
    <doi:10.1080/2330443X.2015.1129918>. Also includes tools for
    computing officers' dynamic exposure to peers' prior behavior, and
    simulating incident-level data for testing and illustration.
